Table Definitions

Legend
ARTS Only
NonARTS
ARTS

Address

Definition: LO_ADS

Definition:A mail location for a party. For example: a customer, supplier, and so on.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
AddressID ID_ADS INTEGER T F F A system assigned identifier for an Address.
AddressTypeCode TY_ADS VARCHAR(30) T F F The type of Address. For example: Postal, Deliveries, Legal Service, and so on. Some of the values for this field are: (-1) UNSPECIFIED, ( 0) HOME, ( 1) WORK, ( 2) OTHER, ( 3) MAIL
PartyID ID_PRTY INTEGER T T F A unique system assigned identifier for a Party.
AddressLine1 A1_CNCT VARCHAR(240) F F T The first line of the Address.
AddressLine2 A2_CNCT VARCHAR(240) F F T The second line of the Address.
AddressLine3 A3_CNCT VARCHAR(240) F F T The third line of the Address.
AddressCity CI_CNCT VARCHAR(120) F F T The city part of the Address.
AddressState ST_CNCT VARCHAR(120) F F T The state part of the Address.
AddressPostalCode PC_CNCT VARCHAR(30) F T T The postal code part of the Address.
AddressTerritory TE_CNCT VARCHAR(120) F F T The territory part of the Address.
AddressCountry CO_CNCT VARCHAR(120) F F T The country part of the Address.
TelephoneCountryCode CC_CNCT VARCHAR(30) F F T The country code part of the telephone number.
TelephoneAreaCode TA_CNCT VARCHAR(30) F F T The area code part of the telephone number.
TelephoneLocalNumber TL_CNCT VARCHAR(30) F F T The local part of the telephone number.

AlterationLineItem

Definition: TR_LTM_ALTR

Definition:A sub-type of RetailTransactionLineItem, which records alteration instructions that are gathered about an item being sold at the POS.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for the RetailStore in which this Transaction was performed.
WorkstationID ID_WS VARCHAR(3) T T F A unique identifier for the Workstation within the confines of the RetailStore in which it is housed.
BusinessDayDate DC_DY_BSN VARCHAR(10) T T F The nominal date of the BusinessDay on which the Transaction was conducted.
TransactionSequenceNumber AI_TRN INTEGER T T F The sequence number of this Transaction, within the confines of the RetailStore, Workstation, and BusinessDay.
RetailTransactionLineItemSequenceNumber AI_LN_ITM SMALLINT T T F A unique identifier for this line item within the confines of the Transaction.
AlterationType TY_ALTR VARCHAR(2) F F T A code denoting the type of alteration to be performed.
ItemDescription DE_ITM VARCHAR(250) F F F The description of the Item being altered.
ItemID ID_ITM VARCHAR(14) F T T A unique system identifier for an Item of merchandise or service.
Value1 DE_VL1 VARCHAR(250) F F T The first part of the alteration instructions.
Value2 DE_VL2 VARCHAR(250) F F T The second part of the alteration instructions.
Value3 DE_VL3 VARCHAR(250) F F T The third part of the alteration instructions.
Value4 DE_VL4 VARCHAR(250) F F T The fourth part of the alteration instructions.
Value5 DE_VL5 VARCHAR(250) F F T The fifth part of the alteration instructions.
Value6 DE_VL6 VARCHAR(250) F F T The sixth part of the alteration instructions.

Application

Definition: CO_APP

Definition:Contains all Applications that Oracle Retail ISO has. It is used to expand the role of a user to be able to use a specific application. For example: Employee 23 can access POS, but cannot access Central Office and Back Office.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
ApplicationID ID_APP INTEGER T F F A system assigned identifier for the Application.
ApplicationName APP_NM VARCHAR(120) F F F The name of the Application.

ApplicationLog

Definition: CO_APP_LOG

Definition:This table is used for auditing purposes. If this feature is enabled for logging and it is turned ON, the system will log every aspect of the feature so that it can then be reproduced step by step at a later time.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
ApplicationLogID ID_APP_LOG INTEGER T F F A system assigned identifier for the ApplicationLog.
ApplicationLogCategory CTGY_APP_LOG INTEGER F F F The ApplicationLog category. Possible values: 1 = Audit
ApplicaitonLogMessageDate DC_MSG_LOG TIMESTAMP F F F The date and time when the ApplicationLog message was created.
EmployeeLogID ID_EM_LOG VARCHAR(10) F F T The identifier of the Employee causing the generation of the log message. If the column is set to NULL, the message was system generated.
LogMessageType TY_MSG_LOG VARCHAR(40) F F F The type of log message. Some values are: Returns Management
LogMessageID ID_MSG_LOG VARCHAR(40) F F F An identifier for the log message being generated.
LogMessage DE_MSG_LOG CLOB F F F The body of the log message. The format of the main message is in XML.

ApplicationSchemaVersioning

Definition: CO_APP_SCH_VER

Definition:This table is not used. This table is used for schema upgrade purposes, it contains the revision level of the schema. The schema will support the following format example: 12.1.0.0
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
ApplicationProductID ID_APP_PRD INTEGER T F F A unique system assigned identifier for the ApplicationProduct. The initial product is the ISO database schema and it has a value of 1.
NameApplicationProduct NM_APP_PRD VARCHAR(30) F F F The name of the ApplicationProduct schema. Example: ISO - In-Store Operations schema
ReleaseLevelBaseProduct REL_BS_PRD INTEGER F F F Contains the release level of the base schema. This is the first component of the version display: 12.1.0.0 Example: 12
VersionLevelBaseProduct VER_BS_PRD INTEGER F F F Contains the version level of the base schema. This is the second component of the version display: 12.1.0.0 Example: 1
PatchLevelBaseProduct PTCH_BS_PRD INTEGER F F F Contains the patch level of the base schema. This is the third component of the version display: 12.1.0.0 Example: 0
BuildLevelBaseProduct BLD_BS_PRD INTEGER F F F Contains the build level of the base schema. This is the third component of the version display: 12.1.0.0 Example: 0
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F F The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F F The date and time this record was last modified.

AssociatedRetailStoreGroup

Definition: ST_ASCTN_STRGP

Definition:An associative entity resolving the recursive-many-to-many relationship on RetailStoreGroup. It denotes a parent and child relationship between two RetailStoreGroups for a particular RetailStoreGroupFunction. Each child RetailStoreGroup will have a different parent RetailStoreGroup for each RetailStoreGroupFunction that is defined.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreGroupFunctionID ID_STRGP_FNC INTEGER T T F A unique system assigned identifier for a RetailStoreGroupFunction.
RetailStoreGroupParentID ID_STRGP_PRNT VARCHAR(14) T T F A unique system assigned identifier for the parent RetailStoreGroup.
RetailStoreGroupChildID ID_STRGP_CHLD VARCHAR(14) T T F A unique system assigned identifier for the child RetailStoreGroup.
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

AssociatedRetailStoreStoreGroup

Definition: ST_ASCTN_STRGP_STR

Definition:An associative entity resolving the many-to-many relationship between a RetailStore and a RetailStoreGroup, allowing a RetailStore to be a member of more than one RetailStoreGroup. It is expected that a particular store will be a member of only one RetailStoreGroup for any particular RetailStoreGroupFunction.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
RetailStoreGroupID ID_STRGP VARCHAR(14) T T F A unique system assigned identifier for the RetailStoreGroup.
RetailStoreGroupFunctionID ID_STRGP_FNC INTEGER T T F A unique system assigned identifier for a RetailStoreGroupFunction.
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

AuditLog

Definition: ADT_LOG

Definition:A log of interesting events such as tracking the behavior of various Employees.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
AuditLogID ID_ADT_LOG INTEGER T F F A unique system assigned identifier for the AuditLog.
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
EmployeeID ID_EM VARCHAR(10) F T F A unique system assigned identifier for an Employee.
RecordType TYP_RCRD INTEGER F F T The type of record getting recorded.
FieldName FLD_NM VARCHAR(40) F F T The name of the field being audited.
OriginalValue VL_ORGL VARCHAR(40) F F T The original value in the field.
NewValue VL_NW VARCHAR(40) F F T The new value for the field.
ObjectID ID_OBJ VARCHAR(10) F F T A unique identifier for the object.
ReasonCodeID ID_RSN_CD INTEGER F F T A unique identifier for the reason code.
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

BundleImportStatus

Definition: MA_STS_BNDL_IMP

Definition:A table containing the DIMP import status for bundle jar files.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
BundleID ID_BNDL VARCHAR(20) F F F An external identifier sent within a bundle and optionally as part of the bundle name. Used to distinguish bundles from one another.
BundleFileName NM_BNDL_IMP VARCHAR(60) F F F The bundle name. The default format is [arbitrary_portion]-[store_id]-[YYYYMMDD]-[NNN].jar
ArchiveStatus SC_STS_BNDL VARCHAR(20) F F F A string describing whether the bundle was processed. Values are PROCESSING, PROCESSED, FAILED, and INCONSISTENT ARCHIVE.
ArchivedFileName NM_BNDL_ARCH VARCHAR(60) F F T The name given to the bundle when it is moved to the archive location
StartProcessingTime TS_STR_IMP_PRC TIMESTAMP F F T The begin time of bundle processing.
EndProcessingTime TS_END_IMP_PRC TIMESTAMP F F T The end time of bundle processing.
BundleRetryCount QU_BNDL_RTRY_CNT INTEGER F F T The number of times processing attempts have been made on the bundle.
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

BusinessCustomer

Definition: ORGN_CT

Definition:A (nominal) sub-type of Customer which is not a person but a company or other organization.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
OrganizationID ID_ORGN INTEGER T F F An identifier for the Organization.
PartyID ID_PRTY INTEGER T T F A unique system assigned identifier for a Party.
OrganizationName ORGN_NAME VARCHAR(120) F F T The name of the organization.
TaxExemptionCertificate TX_EXM_CF VARCHAR(30) F F T The serial number on the Organization's tax exemption certificate.
ExemptionReason EXM_RSN VARCHAR(30) F F T A code denoting the reason the Organization has a tax exemption.

BusinessDay

Definition: CA_DY_BSN

Definition:A calendar date that corresponds to an accounting period fiscal day at a particular RetailStore, has financial Transactions attributed to it, is aggregated using the CalendarPeriod structure, and is opened and closed every day through the StoreOpenCloseTransaction.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
BusinessDayDate DC_DY_BSN VARCHAR(10) T F F The nominal date of the current BusinessDay.
FiscalDayNumber WD_DY_FSC CHAR(1) F F T The fiscal day of the week that this BusinessDay falls into.
FiscalWeekNumber FW_NMB VARCHAR(2) F F T The fiscal week of the year that this BusinessDay falls into.
FiscalYear FY VARCHAR(4) F F T The fiscal year that this BusinessDay falls into.

BusinessDayBatchCount

Definition: CA_DY_BSN_BTCH

Definition:This table keeps a count of the number of batches that are exported to the RTLog during each business day.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
BusinessDayDate DC_DY_BSN VARCHAR(10) T T F The nominal date of the current BusinessDay.
BatchCount QU_BTCH_TOT INTEGER F F T The count of the number of batches that are exported to the RTLog during each business day

Calendar

Definition: CA_CLD

Definition:A business function for which a specific Calendar is maintained within the retail enterprise. For example: Merchandising, SalesTax, Payroll, Promotions, Sales Reporting.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
CalendarID ID_CLD INTEGER T F F A system assigned identifier for the business function Calendar.
CalendarName NM_CLD VARCHAR(120) F F T A name for the Calendar business function.
CalendarGranularityCode CD_CLD_GRN VARCHAR(6) F F T A code denoting the smallest period of time defined by the Calendar.
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

CalendarLevel

Definition: CA_CLD_LV

Definition:A level of roll-up within a particular Calendar. For example: MerchandisingCalendar may have Weeks, SubSeason, Seasons, and Years. Payroll Calendar may have Months and Years. SalesTax Calendar may have Quarters and Years.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
CalendarID ID_CLD INTEGER T T F A system assigned identifier for the business function Calendar.
CalendarLevelID ID_CLD_LV INTEGER T F F A system assigned identifier for the CalendarLevel within the Calendar.
CalendarLevelName NM_CLD_LV VARCHAR(120) F F T The name of the CalendarLevel.
PeriodBoundaryCode CD_PRD_BNDY VARCHAR(6) F F T A code denoting what the boundary is for each CalendarPeriod defined to be in this CalendarLevel.
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

CalendarLevelAssociation

Definition: ST_ASCTN_CLD_LV

Definition:A collection of monetary and operational totals used to track the activity volume for the Retail Store during a reporting period. Tracked are transactions of these types: Sale, Return, Exchange, LayawayPickup (same as LayawayComplete), Special Order Complete and Void.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
ReportingPeriodID ID_PRD_RP INTEGER T T F A system assigned identifier for a ReportingPeriod.
SalesTransactionCount QU_SLS_TRN DECIMAL(9,2) F F T The number of transactions where items from the Retail Store were sold during the ReportingPeriod. Transactions include Sale, Layaway Pickup and Order Complete transactions minus those that were Post Voided
ItemSalesUnitCount QU_SLS_ITM DECIMAL(9,2) F F T The number of items sold from the Retail Store during the ReportingPeriod. Items included are units from Sale, Layaway Pickup, and Order Complete transactions less units from Post Void transactions.
TotalSalesAmount MO_SLS_TOT DECIMAL(13,2) F F T The monetary value of items sold from the Retail Store during the ReportingPeriod. Value includes taxable and non taxable amounts from Sale, Layaway Pickup, Order Complete transactions less the amounts from those transactions that were PostVoided. The value does not include tax.
TotalReturnAmount MO_RTN_TOT DECIMAL(13,2) F F T The monetary value of items returned from the Retail Store during the ReportingPeriod. Includes non-taxable and taxable return amounts in Sale and Return transactions, less any return amounts in those transactions that were Post Voided. The value does not include tax.
RecordCreateTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created
RecordModifyTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

Layaway

Definition: AS_LY

Definition:Record of a delayed purchase, whereby a Customer chooses an Item for purchase and pays for it over a period of time. The Customer does not receive the Item until it has been fully paid for. Any money received in consideration for the Layway must be treated as a liability in the general ledger, until the item is uplifted.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
LayawayID ID_LY VARCHAR(30) T F F A unique system assigned identifier for the Layaway.
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) F T F A unique identifier for the particular RetailStore in the enterprise, at which this Transaction was performed
CustomerID ID_CT VARCHAR(14) F T T A unique system assigned identifier for the Customer who is conducting the Layaway.
LaywayStatus ST_LY SMALLINT F F T A code denoting the status of the Layaway. The possible values are: (0) Undefined (1) New (2) Active (3) Expired (4) Completed (5) Deleted (6) Voided (7) SuspendedCanceled (8) SuspendedRetrieved
PreviousLayawayStatus ST_LY_PREV SMALLINT F F T The status of the Layaway prior to this Transaction commencing. Possible values are: (0) Undefined (1) New (2) Active (3) Expired (4) Completed (5) Deleted (6) Voided (7) SuspendedCanceled (8) SuspendedRetrieved
LayawayStatusModificationTimestamp TS_MDF_ST TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time when the Layaway was last modified.
LayawayExpirationDate DT_LY_EP DATE F F T The date that the Layaway will expire automatically, if the Customer does not complete payment.
LayawayGracePeriodDate DT_LY_GPD DATE F F T The date that the 'grace period' expires, after which the Layaway will be cancelled.
LayawayMinimumDownPayment MO_PYM_LY_MNM_DWN DECIMAL(13,2) F F T The current minimum down payment that the Customer must make to keep the Layaway alive.
LayawayStorageLocation NM_LCN_STR VARCHAR(60) F F T A code denoting the inventory storage location that the merchandise is being stored, until the Layaway is completed or cancelled.
LayawayTotal MO_LY_TOT DECIMAL(13,2) F F T The total monetary value of the Layaway.

POSIdentity

Definition: ID_IDN_PS

Definition:A simple cross-reference between the barcode, point of sale scan code, or other keyed identifying number used at POS and the internal stock keeping ItemID for the item. The POSItemID will generally be filled with the GTIN (UPC, EAN, and so on) for an item, but it is not mandatory. A retailer may develop and maintain its own set of POS identifiers.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
POSItemID ID_ITM_POS VARCHAR(14) T F F A primary token identifier for an Item, used to facilitate price lookup. Normally this will be the UPC or EAN barcode placed on the Item by the manufacturer.
ItemID ID_ITM VARCHAR(14) T T F A unique system identifier for an Item of merchandise or service.
ItemDescription DE_ITM_POS VARCHAR(250) F F T A short description of the Item being identified.
CurrentSaleUnitPOSRetailPriceAmount RP_SLS_POS_CRT DECIMAL(8,2) F F T The current retail price per sale unit of the Item identified by this POSIdentity. This monetary amount is used as the basis for deriving retail price at the point of sale.
FrequentShopperPointsEligibleFlag FL_PNT_FQ_SHPR_EL CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether the Item identified by this POSIdentity is eligible for frequent shopper benefits as part of a customer loyalty scheme.
ManufacturerID ID_MF INTEGER F F T A retailer assigned identifier for the Manufacturer of the Item identified by this POSIdentity.
ManufacturerUPC ID_ITM_MF_UPC VARCHAR(14) F F T The manufacturer assigned unique identifier for the Item being identified by this POSIdentity.
ReturnAgentID ID_AGNT_RTN INTEGER F F T A retailer assigned identifier for the party to whom returns of this Item are sent.
CustomerAffiliationDiscountAllowedFlag FL_DSC_AF_DSC_ALW CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting PriceDerivationRule applicability to a customer group affiliation for the Item identified by this POSIdentity.
CouponValueCode LU_VT_PS_CPN CHAR(2) F F T A two digit value code that designates the redemption value of a coupon in monetary units. The code follows the family code on the UPC/EAN coupon code. The code in some instances is a direct representation of the face value (code number 10 represents a 10 cent coupon value) and some which are not (code number 83 represents $2.25coupon value).
CouponEndOfOfferDate DT_END_PS_CPN_OFR VARCHAR(4) F F T The end of offer date encoded in the supplementary part of the coupon code. This code provides the month and year. Example: 0697 denotes the expiration date for that particular coupon as June 30, 1997.
MinimumSaleUnitCount QU_UN_BLK_MNM DECIMAL(5,2) F F T For Items, the minimum number of selling units (Examples: square yards, linear feet, pounds, liters) that must be purchased for a specific Item. This selling rule qualifies the Item at point of sale.
MarketBasketDiscountAllowedFlag FL_DSC_MRK_BSK_ALW CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting the PriceDerivationRule applicability to a market basket for the Item.
CustomerAccountDiscountAllowedFlag FL_DSC_CT_ACNT_ALW CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting the PriceDerivationRule applicability to a particular customer account for the Item.
MaximumSaleUnitCount QU_UN_BLK_MXM DECIMAL(5,2) F F T Defines the maximum number of retail sale units that may be purchased in a single sales Transaction. Typically this is used for special promotions or "rationed" merchandise. Example: Nintendo 64 in Christmas 1995. A value of -1 means unlimited
EmployeeDiscountAllowedFlag FL_DSC_EM_ALW CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting the PriceDerivationRule applicability to a particular Employee for the Item.
AllowCouponMultiplyFlag FL_CPN_ALW_MULTY CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting multiple coupon promotions. Used to enable or disable double or triple coupon promotions.
AllowFoodStampFlag FL_FD_STP_ALW CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether food stamps can be tendered for this Item.
ElectronicCouponFlag FL_CPN_ELNTC CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether an electronic coupon is available for this Item. The value is automatically applied to the purchase, no media is exchanged.
CouponRestrictedFlag FL_CPN_RST CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether a coupon can be redeemed for this Item.
PriceEntryRequiredFlag FL_ENTR_PRC_RQ CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting that the retail price has to manually entered when this Item is purchased by a Customer.
WeightEntryRequiredFlag FL_QR_ENR_WT CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting that the weight of this Item has to be entered into the system to derive the selling price.
QuantityKeyProhibitFlag FL_KY_PRH_QTY CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting that the quantity key cannot be used with the sale of this Item.
ProhibitReturnFlag FL_RTN_PRH CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether this Item can be returned unless faulty. This normally applies to freezer or chilled products.
GiveawayFlag FL_ITM_GWY CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether this Item can be given away free as part of a promotion, provided the Customer fully meets the conditions of that promotion.
WICFlag FL_ITM_WIC CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if this Item is allowed in a WIC Transaction.
VisualVerifyPriceFlag FL_PRC_VS_VR CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether the Operator must verify the price in the Item with the price derived from the price lookup table.
ProhibitRepeatKeyFlag FL_KY_PRH_RPT CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether to prohibit the use of the repeat key when selling this Item. This flag forces the Operator to scan or separately enter each instance of an Item rather than use a repeat key to ensure inventory integrity and avoid arithmetic errors.
SpecialOrderEligibleFlag FL_SPO_ITM CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether the Item identified by this POSIdentity can be the subject of a special customer order.
FrequentShopperPointsCount QU_PNT_FQ_SHPR DECIMAL(9,2) F F T The number of frequent buyer points awarded for purchase of this Item.
ItemTenderRestrictionGroupCode LU_GP_TND_RST VARCHAR(20) F F T A code to denote a specific group of Item tender restrictions that apply to the Item identified by this POSIdentity.
ManufacturerFamilyCode FC_FMY_MF VARCHAR(3) F F T The UPC designated three digit coupon family code for the manufacturer item.
PriceModifiableFlag FL_MDFR_RT_PRC CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting whether the Item identified by this POSIdentity, may have it's lookup price overridden at the POS.
PromotionID ID_PRM INTEGER F F F The PromotionIdentifier associated with an RMS promotion. This value will be sent to ReSA in the RTLog if this PriceDerivationRule is applied to a line item in a transaction. Values: 1004 - In Store Discount 9999 - Promotion
PromotionComponentID ID_PRM_CMP INTEGER F F F The PromotionComponentIdentifier associated with an RMS promotion. This value will be sent to ReSA in the RTLog if this PriceDerivationRule is applied to a line item in a transaction. If the PromotionID contains the value 9999, this field contains the promotion component value associated with the promotion.
PromotionComponentDetailID ID_PRM_CMP_DTL INTEGER F F F The PromotionComponentDetailIdentifier associated with an RMS promotion.
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

PriceDerivationRule

Definition: RU_PRDV

Definition:The specification of a method to be used to transform the current sell unit retail amount to the retail price actually paid by a customer at the point of sale.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
PriceDerivationRuleID ID_RU_PRDV INTEGER T F F A unique identifier for a PriceDerivationRule.
TransactionControlBreakCode LU_CBRK_PRDV_TRN VARCHAR(2) F F F A code denoting when, during the entry of a sale Transaction, this rule will be applied. For example a price change rule may be applied on a line item by line item basis (DETAIL TIME), a price change rule may be triggered after a Transaction is totaled, but before tax and tender entry (SUBTOTAL TIME).
StatusCode SC_RU_PRDV VARCHAR(20) F F F Defines the current status for the PriceDerivationRule. Possible values include: (0) Pending (1) Active (2) Inactive (3) Canceled (4) Expired
TypeCode TY_RU_PRDV VARCHAR(2) F F F A code denoting the type of PriceDerivationRule. Values are: 'IT' - Item 'MM' - Mix and Match
ExpirationDate DC_RU_PRDV_EP TIMESTAMP F F F The date this PriceDerivationRule is no longer able to be applied.
EffectiveDate DC_RU_PRDV_EF TIMESTAMP F F F The date from which this PriceDerivationRule is able to be applied.
PriceDerivationRuleDescription DE_RU_PRDV VARCHAR(250) F F F A description of the PriceDerivationRule. Note: This description must match the column NM_TY_PRDV in table RU_TY_PRDV(PriceDerivationRuleType)
EventID ID_EV INTEGER F T T A unique system assigned identifier for the last Event, which modified or created this PriceDerivationRule.
PriceDerivationRuleName NM_RU_PRDV VARCHAR(120) F F F The name of the PriceDerivationRule.
ReasonCode RC_RU_PRDV INTEGER F F F A code detailing the reason for applying this PriceDerivationRule.
AdvancedDealAppliedFlag FL_DL_ADVN_APLY CHAR(1) F F F A flag denoting if a PriceDerivationRule is used in the Best Pricing computations.
AssignmentBasisCode CD_BAS_PRDV INTEGER F F T A code denoting the basis on which the PriceDerivationRule is assigned to a LineItem. Possible values include: (0) Manual (1) Customer (2) Item (3) Store Coupon (4) Other (5) Employee
ScopeCode CD_SCP_PRDV INTEGER F F T A code denoting the scope of any discount granted by this PriceDerivationRule. Possible values include: (0) Transaction (1) Item (2) Group
MethodCode CD_MTH_PRDV INTEGER F F T A code denoting what sort of discount is to be granted with this PriceDerivationRule. Possible values include: (UN) NotInUse (PE) ByPercentage (AM) ByAmount (FP) FixedPrice
DefaultEntryCode FL_CD_ENT_DFLT CHAR(1) F F F The default entry code used by the Oracle Retail Back Office UI.
DepartmentLedgerStockModifier DP_LDG_STK_MDFR VARCHAR(20) F F F A code that determines how the price change reflected in this modifier is to be treated for stock ledger accounting purposes. This code allows price change modifiers to be treated as discounts (expenses below the gross margin line) or as markdowns (treated as changes to the inventory value which alter the stock ledgers cumulative markdown for the item). This code reflects the setting of AccountingDispositionCode in the promotion that caused the price modification at the time of the retail Transaction.
ListSortIndex CD_ENT_SRT SMALLINT F F F An index used by the UI to sort the PriceDerivationRules.
Application Limit QU_LM_APLY SMALLINT F F F Indicates the number of times a rule can be applied. The default is -1 which indicates no limit.
SourceThresholdAmount MO_TH_SRC DECIMAL(13,2) F F F The lower limit of the boundary criteria.
SourceLimitAmount MO_LM_SRC DECIMAL(13,2) F F F The upper limit of the boundary criteria.
TargetThresholdAmount MO_TH_TGT DECIMAL(13,2) F F F The lower limit of the target amount.
TargetLimitAmount MO_LM_TGT DECIMAL(13,2) F F F The upper limit of the target amount.
PriceDerivationThresholdTypeCode CD_TY_TH_PRDV VARCHAR(4) F F F The boundary type, whether amount or quantity.
DealDistributionFlag FL_DL_DST CHAR(1) F F T The deal distribution indicator provides the ability to prorate the discount across all targets and sources. Values are Target and Source, and Target. Default is Target.
AllowRepeatingSourcesFlag FL_ALW_RPT_SRC CHAR(1) F F T The allow repeating sources indicator provides the ability to prevent the triggering of a deal when a Customer purchases multiples of the same source Item or where X can be a department or class.
DiscountTypeID ID_TY_DISC INTEGER F F F The type of discount. Possible values are Discount amount, or Fixed Price.
SourceComparisonBasisCode CD_BAS_CMP_SRC VARCHAR(20) F F T A code denoting the comparison basis that was used when applying this PriceDerivationRule to the source. Possible values include: (0) ItemID (1) DepartmentID (2) MerchandiseClass
TargetComparisonBasisCode CD_BAS_CMP_TGT VARCHAR(20) F F T A code denoting the comparison basis that was used when applying this PriceDerivationRule to the target. Possible values include: (0) ItemID (1) DepartmentID (2) MerchandiseClass
PromotionID ID_PRM INTEGER F F F The PromotionIdentifier associated with an RMS promotion. This value will be sent to ReSA in the RTLog if this PriceDerivationRule is applied to a line item in a transaction. Values: 1004 - In Store Discount 9999 - Promotion
PromotionComponentID ID_PRM_CMP INTEGER F F F The PromotionComponentIdentifier associated with an RMS promotion. This value will be sent to ReSA in the RTLog if this PriceDerivationRule is applied to a line item in a transaction. If the PromotionID contains the value 9999, this field contains the promotion component value associated with the promotion.
PromotionComponentDetailID ID_PRM_CMP_DTL INTEGER F F F The PromotionComponentDetailIdentifier associated with an RMS promotion.
SourceAnyQuantity QU_AN_SRC SMALLINT F F T The source quantity when a rule is of type 'Any'. For example: Buy(AnyOneFromList)GetXat50%off. Values: 0 - All items in the list are required. 1 or more - The number of source items required.
TargetAnyQuantity QU_AN_TGT SMALLINT F F T The target quantity when a rule is of type 'Any'. For example: BuyXGet(AnyOneFromList)at 50%off. Values: 0 - All items in the list. 1 or more - The number of target items allowed.
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

Definition: RU_TY_PRDV

Definition:Contains the list of valid PriceDerivationRule types.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition

RMKPIParameter

Definition: RM_KPI_PRMR

Central Office Only

Definition:Values for all the KPI Parameters.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
KPIParameterID ID_KPI_PRMR INTEGER T F F A system assigned identifier for the RMKPIParameter.
KPID ID_KPI INTEGER F T T A system assigned identifier for the RMKeyPerformanceIndicator.
KPIParameterName NM_PRMR VARCHAR(32) F F F The KPI parameter name visible on the screen.
KPIParameterValueType TY_PRMR_VAL INTEGER F F F The type of value: int, string, date
KPIParameterDefaultValue DE_DFLT_VAL VARCHAR(128) F F F The default value for the RMKPIParameter.
ConfigurableParameterFlag FL_CFG_PRMR CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if this RMKPIParameter is configurable for rule evaluation and penalty box.
ParameterUsageType TY_PRMR INTEGER F F F Usage type: This is a bit mapped integer whose values are derived from KPIIfc.java. The current supported bit values are as follows: TYPE_RULE_EVALUATION = 1 TYPE_PENALTY_BOX = 2 TYPE_CUMULATIVE_EXCEPTION_COUNT = 4 TYPE_ALERT = 8 The value stored in the database is the bitwise OR value of these flags. A value of 3 indicates both rule evaluation and penalty box functionality is supported by the parameter. The values that I currently see in the database correspond to this bit mapped structure and suggest that the TYPE_ALERT value is not in use yet. The current list of values are: 1, 2, 3, 4, and 7.

RMReturnResponseCode

Definition: RM_RSPS_RC

Central Office Only

Definition:The response code to send back to a request for a return when a customer is in a penalty period.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
ResponseCode ID_RSPS_RC INTEGER T F F A system assigned identifier for the RMResponseCode.
ResponseType TY_RSPS VARCHAR(25) F F F The RMResponseCode type: Authorization, Contingent Authorization, Mgr Overrideable Denial, Denial
Priority PRITY_RSPS INTEGER F F F RMResponseCodes are prioritized within Response Types. No two response codes of the same Response Type can have the same priority. As the analytic engine evaluates policy rules, the system holds the highest priority response code within that Response Type as the response, until a rule resulting in a higher Response Type, with a higher priority, supersedes it, thus the retailer can control whether the most favorable or least favorable response is returned to the point-of-sale or return.

RetailStoreGroupFunction

Definition: CO_STRGP_FNC

Definition:A business function for which RetailStores are placed into a separate grouping hierarchy. For example: Taxation: The stores are placed into groups along the boundaries of various TaxAuthorities - State, County, and City. Merchandising: The stores are placed into groups along the boundaries of various climatic regions, - East Coast, Mid-West, Pacific NorthWest. With the implication being that umbrellas sell very well in Washington state all year round, while they do not sell at all in Texas.

Definition:A summary of all activity that has occurred at a particular Retail Store over a ReportingPeriod.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
FiscalYear FY VARCHAR(4) T T F The fiscal year the ReportingPeriod falls into.
ReportingPeriodTypeCode TY_PR_PRD VARCHAR(2) T T F A code denoting a particular type of ReportingPeriod.
ReportingPeriodID ID_PR_PRD INTEGER T T F A system assigned identifier for a ReportingPeriod.
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
OperatorID ID_OPR VARCHAR(10) F T T A unique identifier for the Operator within the confines of a single RetailStore.
TotalTenderLoanCount QU_LON_TND_TOT INTEGER F F T The number of tender loans performed during the ReportingPeriod.
StartDateTimestamp TS_TM_SRT TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time at start of period.

TaxGroupRule

Definition: RU_TX_GP

Definition:A rule that prescribes how a particular tax is to be applied to a group of Items on behalf of a particular TaxAuthority.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
TaxAuthorityID ID_ATHY_TX INTEGER T T F A unique system assigned identifier for a government taxation authority, on behalf of whom the retailer collects sales and other taxes, and who specifies this TaxGroupRule.
TaxGroupID ID_GP_TX INTEGER T T F A unique system assigned identifier for the group of taxable items, to which this TaxGroupRule applies.
TaxTypeID TY_TX INTEGER T T F A unique system assigned identifier for the TaxType.
TaxHolidayFlag FLG_TX_HDY CHAR(1) T F F A flag denoting if the tax rule is a tax holiday. If it is a tax holiday, then any non-tax holiday rules will be ignored.
TaxRuleName NM_RU_TX VARCHAR(120) F F T The name of the TaxGroupRule
TaxRuleDescription DE_RU_TX VARCHAR(250) F F T The description of the TaxGroupRule.
CompoundSequenceNumber AI_CMPND SMALLINT F F F An integer that indicates the order to which multiple applicable TaxGroupRules should be applied. Example: City, County, and State TaxGroupRules are not compounding. All three rules will contain zero (or NULL) for this value. Example: PST and GST TaxGroupRules are to be applied in a compounding fashion with PST going first - The rule for PST will contain 1 for this value, the rule for GST will contain 2 for this value.
TaxOnGrossAmountFlag FL_TX_GS_AMT CHAR(1) F F F A flag denoting that the TaxGroupRule is to be applied to the gross amount of the items being sold. For example: before any discounts, price rules or deals have been applied to the regular retail price. Values: 0 - tax on extended discounted selling price ,(SaleReturnLineItemExtendedDiscountedAmount) 1 - tax on regular unit price
CalculationMethodCode CD_CAL_MTH INTEGER F F F A code denoting how the TaxGroupRule is to be applied in a single transaction. Possible values include: 1 - Calculate and round at line item unit level 2 - Calculate and round at the group level There is no default value, as this setting is dictated by the TaxAuthority who defines the rule.
TaxRateRuleUsageCode CD_TX_RT_RU_USG INTEGER F F F A code denoting how the TaxRateRules are to be applied within the confines of this TaxGroupRule. Possible values are: 1 - Pick one (default), 2 - Use as taxation table (for amount above threshold), 3 - Use as taxation table (for multiples of threshold)
InclusiveTaxFlag FL_TX_INC CHAR(1) F F F A boolean flag to indicate if the tax amount is already included in the item price. Possible values are: '0' Tax amount not included (default) '1' Tax amount included
RecordCreatedTimestamp TS_CRT_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was created.
RecordLastModifiedTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified.

AllowOverride OVERRIDE SMALLINT F F T Appears to be unused.

Workstation

Definition: AS_WS

Definition:A POS, Register, or other terminal used by an Operator to enter data into the retailer's systems.

WorkstationOpenCloseTransaction

Definition: TR_WS_OPN_CL

Definition:A sub-type of ControlTransaction, that records the opening and closing of a Workstation session, at the beginning and end of a BusinessDay.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for the RetailStore in which this Transaction was performed.
WorkstationID ID_WS VARCHAR(3) T T F A unique identifier for the Workstation within the confines of the RetailStore in which it is housed.
BusinessDayDate DC_DY_BSN VARCHAR(10) T T F The nominal date of the BusinessDay on which the Transaction was conducted.
TransactionSequenceNumber AI_TRN INTEGER T T F The sequence number of this Transaction, within the confines of the RetailStore, Workstation, and BusinessDay.
TransactionTimestamp TS_TM_TRN TIMESTAMP T F F The date and time when the open or close workstation transaction took place.
OperatorID ID_OPR VARCHAR(10) F T T A unique identifier for the Operator within the confines of a single RetailStore.
TransactionTypeCode TY_TRN VARCHAR(20) F F T A code denoting what kind of Transaction this is. Possible values include: (8) OpenRegister (9) CloseRegister
TerminalStatusCode SC_TML_WS INTEGER F F T The status of the Workstation at the time of the Transaction
RecordedWorkstationID ID_WS_RCRD VARCHAR(3) F F F The unique identifier for the Workstation which was actually closed rather than the Workstation at which the CloseWorkstation was actually entered.
RecordedTransactionSequenceNumber AI_TRN_RCRD INTEGER F F F The sequence number of this Transaction, which actually closed the Workstation rather than the Workstation at which the CloseWorkstationTransaction was actually entered.
TrainingModeFlag FL_MOD_TRG CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting the training state of the Workstation at the time of the transaction.
UniqueIdentifierExtension EXT_ID_UNQ VARCHAR(4) F F T An extension on the WorkstationID - used to ensure uniqueness of Workstation identifier.
AccountabilityCode CD_ACT CHAR(1) F F T A code denoting the style of accountability the Workstation is operating under. Possible values include Till or Operator.
TillFloatAmount CP_BLNC_DFLT_OPN DECIMAL(13,2) F F T The amount of cash that must be placed in the Till before opening it.
CountTillAtCloseCode CD_CL_TL_CNT CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if the cash in the Till must be counted when the Workstation is closed.
CountFloatAtOpenCode CD_OPN_FLT_CNT CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if the extra cash in the Till must be counted at Workstation open.
CountFloatAtCloseCode CD_CL_FLT_CNT CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if the extra cash in the Till must be counted at Workstation close.
CountCashLoanCode CD_LON_CSH_CNT CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if the cash being loaned from the StoreSafe must be counted into the Till.
CountCashPickupCode CD_PKP_CSH_CNT CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if the cash being picked up from the Till should be counted.
CountCheckPickupCode CD_PKP_CHK_CNT CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if the Checks being picked up from the Till should be counted
TillReconcileFlag FL_RCNL_TL CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if the Till must be reconciled before this Workstation can be closed.
WorkstationActiveStatusFlag FL_ACT_WS CHAR(1) F F T A flag denoting if the Workstation is active.

WorkstationProductivitySummary

Definition: LE_SMY_WS_TMACV

Definition:A summary of the activity that occurred at a Register (Workstation), in a 15 minute reporting interval - Maintained by the StoreServer. Tracked are transactions of these types: Sale, Return, Exchange, LayawayPickup (same as LayawayComplete), Special Order Complete and Void.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
RetailStoreID ID_STR_RT VARCHAR(5) T T F A unique identifier for a RetailStore.
ReportingPeriodID ID_PRD_RP INTEGER T T F A system assigned identifier for a ReportingPeriod.
TimePeriodID ID_PRD_TM INTEGER T F F A system allocted identifier for a short time period. (15 minutes)
WorkstationID ID_WS VARCHAR(3) T T F A unique identifier for the Workstation within the confines of the RetailStore in which it is housed.
WorstationActivityStartTime TM_SRT_WS_TMACV VARCHAR(5) F F T The date and time at the start of the TimePeriod interval. Stored in the format "HH:MM".
WorkstationActivityEndTime TM_END_WS_TMACV VARCHAR(5) F F T The date and time of at the end of the TimePeriod interval. Stored in the format "HH:MM".
WorkstationActivityTransactionCount QU_WS_ACV_SLS_TRN DECIMAL(9,2) F F T The number of transactions where items were sold at the given Workstation during the given TimePeriod. Transactions include Sale, Layaway Pickup and Order Complete transactions minus those that were Post Voided.
WorkstationActivityItemUnitCount QU_WS_ACV_SLS_ITM DECIMAL(9,2) F F T The number of items sold at the given Workstation during the given TimePeriod. Items included are units from Sale, Layaway Pickup, and Order Complete transactions less units from Post Void transactions.
WorkstationActivityTotalSalesAmount MO_WS_ACV_SLS_TOT DECIMAL(13,2) F F T The monetary value of items sold at the given Workstation during the given TimePeriod. Value includes taxable and non taxable amounts from Sale, Layaway Pickup, Order Complete transactions less the amounts from those transactions that were PostVoided. The value does not include tax.
WorkstationActivityTotalReturnAmount MO_WS_ACV_RTN_TOT DECIMAL(13,2) F F T The monetary value of items returned at the given Workstation during the given TimePeriod. Includes non-taxable and taxable return amounts in Sale and Return transactions, less any return amounts in those transactions that were Post Voided. The value does not include tax.

RecordModifyTimestamp TS_MDF_RCRD TIMESTAMP F F T The date and time this record was last modified

XMLPReport

Definition: XMLP_RPT

Definition:This table is the main report entity. This table holds information required for processing the report. This table contains the associated ReportDataTemplateID, which is used to identify which data template will be used to generate the data, the associated ReportLayoutID, which is used to identify which layout template will be used to render the report.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
ReportID ID_RPT_XMLP INTEGER T F F A unique identifier for an XMLPReport.
ReportName NM_RPT_XMLP VARCHAR(80) F F T The name of the XMLPReport.
ReportDisplayName NM_DSPL_RPT_XMLP VARCHAR(120) F F T The display name of the XMLPReport.
ReportCategory CTG_RPT_XMLP VARCHAR(50) F F T The report category is used to groups reports, e.g. 'Sales'. One or more reports can have the same category.
ReportDataTemplatelD ID_DT_TMPL_RPT INTEGER F T F A unique identifier for the XMLPReportDataTemplate.
ReportLayoutID ID_LYT_RPT INTEGER F T F A unique identifier for the XMLPReportLayout.
ReportDefaultDatasource NM_DA_DFT_RPT_XMLP VARCHAR(80) F F T This is the datasource to use for the report data. Each report has the ability to use a different datasource.
ReportRoleName NM_RL_RPT_XMLP VARCHAR(50) F F T The role required to access this report.

Definition:This table holds the Ad hoc parameters, if any, that appear on the Ad hoc screen. Each report can be executed using ad hoc parameters.

ReportConfigParameterType TY_CFG_PRMT_RPT VARCHAR(255) F F T

XMLPReportLayout

Definition: XMLP_RPT_LYT

Definition:This table holds the information required for rendering the report. This table holds a layout document which is associated to a report. Before the report is rendered, the export flags, ReportHTMLFlag, ReportPDFFlag, ReportRTFFlag, ReportEXCELFlag and ReportXMLFlag, are checked to determine if the report is allowed be exported in the requested format.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
ReportLayoutID ID_LYT_RPT INTEGER T F F A unique identifier for the XMLPReportLayout.
ReportLayoutName NM_LYT_RPT VARCHAR(80) F F T The name of the XMLPReportLayout.
ReportLayoutType TY_LYT_RPT VARCHAR(20) F F T The type of the layout template, e.g. RTF, XSL
ReportLayoutDocument DO_LYT_RPT BLOB F F T This column holds the layout document in binary format.
ReportHTMLFlag FL_HTML_RPT CHAR(1) F F T This flag indicates if an HTML export is allowed.
ReportPDFFlag FL_PDF_RPT CHAR(1) F F T This flag indicates if a PDF export is allowed.
ReportRTFFlag FL_RTF_RPT CHAR(1) F F T This flag indicates if a RTF export is allowed.
ReportEXCELFlag FL_EXCEL_RPT CHAR(1) F F T This flag indicates if an Excel export is allowed.
ReportXMLFlag FL_XML_RPT CHAR(1) F F T This flag indicates if an XML export is allowed.

XMLPReportLayoutI18N

Definition: XMLP_RPT_LYT_I8

Definition:This table contains a locale specific layout document for each report.
Attribute Column Datatype PK FK NULL Definition
ReportLayoutID ID_LYT_RPT INTEGER T T F A unique identifier for the XMLPReportLayout.
ReportLocale LCL VARCHAR(10) T F F A unique identifier for a human language locale for which translations are available.
ReportLocaleDocument DO_LCL BLOB F F T This column holds the layout document in binary format.
